cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the application of deep learning for retinal disease detection from OCT images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves the use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) and sparsity regularization, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks (cs.NE) and the visualization of lesions using an activation map (cs.MM).
